summary: Former Adelaide Crows captain Rory Sloane has announced his retirement from the AFL due to a serious eye injury. The 33-year-old revealed on Wednesday that he had made the "difficult decision" to end his playing career after suffering a detached retina in his left eye during a training session last month. Sloane, who played 250 games for the Crows over 11 seasons, said the risk of further damage to his eye was too great to continue playing. The announcement comes as a blow to Adelaide, who were hopeful Sloane would be able to return to the field in 2024.

name: Anthony Albanese
summary: Prime Minister Anthony Albanese has addressed gendered violence, calling it a societal issue. He made history by becoming the first sitting PM to trek the Kokoda Track, where he emphasized the importance of Anzac Day and commemorated the people of Papua New Guinea. While on the track, Albanese criticized Elon Musk's handling of the X boss's offensive content removal request, sparking a censorship debate. The Prime Minister also met with PNG Prime Minister James Marape, urging him to resolve conflicts outside of Australia and reiterating the significance of the Kokoda Track in their relationship. Albanese attended the Anzac Day dawn service at Isurava, reaffirming Australia's commitment to remembering PNG's sacrifices.

summary: Rafael Nadal emerged victorious in his Madrid Open match against Darwin Blanch, marking a significant triumph in his preparation for the upcoming French Open. name: Japanese yen
summary: The Japanese yen has depreciated significantly against the US dollar, reaching its lowest level since 1990. This decline is attributed to the divergence in monetary policies between Japan and the United States, with the Bank of Japan maintaining ultra-low interest rates while the Federal Reserve continues to raise rates. Additionally, data indicating persistent inflation in the US has contributed to the dollar's strength. As a result, exchange rates between the Australian dollar and other currencies, including the yen, are being closely monitored. The decline of the yen has prompted concern about possible intervention by Japanese authorities, who have already issued verbal warnings. This situation is being closely watched by international financial markets as it may impact global currency dynamics and economic conditions.
